Extended Data Fig. 1 | Exendin-4 treatment restores AD-induced reductions of 
GLUT3 and PGC-1α expressions in neurons. Primary neurons were isolated from 
embryonic WT mice and APP23 AD mice (E17) then treated with exendin-4 with or 
without compound C, an AMPK inhibitor. Cell lysates were subjected to Western 
blot analysis for detecting GLUT3 (a and b) and PGC-1α (c and d) levels. β-Actin 
was detected as the internal control. n = 3 independent experiments; One-way 
ANOVA followed by Tukey’s multiple comparisons test was performed for 
statistical analysis. All the results are expressed as mean ± s.e.m. C.C: compound C, 
EX-4: exendin-4, GLUT3: glucose transporter 3, PGC-1α: peroxisome proliferator-
activated receptor γ coactivator 1 α.
Nature Aging
Article
https://doi.org/10.1038/s43587-025-00869-3
Extended Data Fig. 2 | The effect of GLP-1RAs on the fatty acid oxidation in 
astrocytes. (a) The measurement of mitochondrial respiration in astrocytes 
isolated from WT mice and APP23 AD mice. Astrocytes were treated with 
exendin-4 and/or compound C. The untreated cells were used as controls. 
Etomoxir, an inhibitor of fatty acid oxidation, was injected before oligomycin 
for the assessment. The oxygen consumption rates (OCR) including basal 
respiration (b), maximal respiration (c), and spare respiratory capacity (d) were 
quantified. (e) The analysis of ATP production. n = 3 independent experiments; 
One-way ANOVA followed by Tukey’s multiple comparisons test. (f and g) Primary 
APP23 mouse astrocytes were isolated and treated with etomoxir to inhibit 
fatty acid oxidation, which subsequently co-cultured with the primary APP23 
mouse neurons with or without exendin-4. The APP CTFs were detected with C20 
antibody. Endogenous BACE1 was detected with anti-BACE1 antibody. β-Actin was 
detected by anti-actin antibody AC-15 as the internal control. n = 3 independent 
experiments; One-way ANOVA followed by Tukey’s multiple comparisons test 
was performed for statistical analysis. (h) Aβ ELISA was conducted to detect 
Aβ40 and Aβ42 in conditioned medium from primary neurons. n = 3 independent 
experiments; One-way ANOVA followed by Tukey’s multiple comparisons test  
was performed for statistical analysis. (i-k) Primary WT mouse neurons were 
treated with exendin-4 with or without AKT (PKB) inhibitor, PKA inhibitor or  
compound C, an AMPK inhibitor. (i) Western blot analysis was performed for 
detecting endogenous BACE1, phosphorylated AMPK and total AMPK levels. 
β-Actin was detected by anti-actin antibody AC-15 as the internal control.  
The ratio of p-AMPK to t-AMPK ( j) and BACE1 expressions (k) were quantified. 
n = 3 independent experiments; one-way ANOVA followed by Tukey's multiple 
comparison test was performed for statistical analysis. All the results are 
expressed as mean ± s.e.m. C.C: compound C, EX-4: exendin-4, OCR: oxygen 
consumption rate.
Nature Aging
Article
https://doi.org/10.1038/s43587-025-00869-3
Extended Data Fig. 3 | The effect of GLP-1RAs on the fatty acid oxidation in 
astrocytes treated with palmitate. (a) The measurement of mitochondrial 
respiration in astrocytes isolated from WT mice and APP23 AD mice.  
Palmitate was applied to the cultured astrocytes treated with exendin-4 and/or  
compound C. (f) Etomoxir, an inhibitor of fatty acid oxidation, was injected 
before oligomycin for the assessment. The oxygen consumption rates (OCR) 
including basal respiration (b and g), maximal respiration (c and h), and spare 
respiratory capacity (d and i) were quantified. (e and j) The analysis of ATP 
production. n = 3 independent experiments; One-way ANOVA followed by 
Tukey’s multiple comparisons test was performed for statistical analysis. All the 
results are expressed as mean ± s.e.m. C.C: compound C, EX-4: exendin-4, OCR: 
oxygen consumption rate.
Nature Aging
Article
https://doi.org/10.1038/s43587-025-00869-3
Extended Data Fig. 4 | The effect of GLP-1RAs on the glycolysis in AD 
astrocytes. (a) The measurement of glycolysis in astrocytes isolated from 
WT mice and APP23 AD mice. Astrocytes were treated with exendin-4 and/
or compound C. The untreated cells were used as controls. The extracellular 
acidification rate (ECAR) including glycolysis (b), glycolytic capacity (c), and  
non-glycolytic acidification (d) were quantified. n = 3 independent experiments; 
One-way ANOVA followed by Tukey’s multiple comparisons test was performed 
for statistical analysis. All the results are expressed as mean ± s.e.m. C.C: 
compound C, EX-4: exendin-4, ECAR: extracellular acidification rate.
