Extended Data Fig. 5 | The effect of GLP-1RAs on the oxidative 
phosphorylation and glycolysis in AD neurons. (a) The measurement of 
mitochondrial respiration in neurons isolated from WT mice and APP23 AD mice. 
Neurons were treated with exendin-4 and/or compound C. The untreated cells 
were used as controls. The oxygen consumption rates (OCR) including basal 
respiration (b), maximal respiration (c), and spare respiratory capacity (d) were 
quantified. (e) The analysis of ATP production. n = 4 independent experiments; 
One-way ANOVA followed by Tukey’s multiple comparisons test was performed 
for statistical analysis. (f) The measurement of glycolysis in neurons isolated 
from WT mice and APP23 AD mice. Neurons were treated with exendin-4  
and/or compound C. The untreated cells were used as controls. The extracellular 
acidification rate (ECAR) including glycolysis (g), glycolytic capacity (h), and 
non-glycolytic acidification (i) were quantified. n = 3 independent experiments; 
One-way ANOVA followed by Tukey’s multiple comparisons test was performed 
for statistical analysis. The expressions of pyruvate (j) and reactive oxygen species 
(k and l) were measured. Scale bar represents 20 μm. n = 9 cells from 3 
independent experiments. One-way ANOVA followed by Tukey’s multiple 
comparisons test was performed for statistical analysis. All the results 
are expressed as mean ± s.e.m. C.C: compound C, EX-4: exendin-4, ECAR: 
extracellular acidification rate, OCR: oxygen consumption rate, ROS: reactive 
oxygen species.
