Article
https://doi.org/10.1038/s43587-025-00869-3
Extended Data Fig. 6 | Reduction of AMPK expression mitigates the impact of 
exendin-4 on BACE1-mediated APP processing. Primary APP23 mouse neurons 
were infected with lentivirus carrying scramble sequence or short-hairpin RNA 
(shRNA) sequence targeting AMPK, with or without treatment of exendin-4.  
(a and b) Western blot analysis was performed for detecting full-length APP, the 
APP CTFs, endogenous BACE1, and total AMPK levels. β-Actin was detected as the 
internal control. n = 3 independent experiments; One-way ANOVA followed by 
Tukey’s multiple comparisons test was performed for statistical analysis.  
(c) Aβ ELISA was conducted to detect Aβ40 and Aβ42 in conditioned medium 
from APP23 neurons. n = 3 independent experiments; One-way ANOVA followed 
by Tukey’s multiple comparisons test was performed for statistical analysis.  
All the results are expressed as mean ± s.e.m. APP: β-amyloid precursor protein, 
Aβ: Amyloid β protein, BACE1: beta site APP cleaving enzyme 1, EX-4: exendin-4.
