Extended Data Fig. 8 | The effects of GLP-1RAs on inflammation. BV2 cells 
were pre-treated with exendin-4 or tirzepatide before being cultured with Aβ 
oligomers for 24 hours with or without the presence of compound C. The levels  
of IL-1β (a), IL-6 (b), TNF (c) and TGF-β (d) were measured by performing ELISA. 
n = 4 independent experiments; A two-tailed student’s t-test was performed  
for statistical analysis. All the results are expressed as mean ± s.e.m. C.C: 
compound C, EX-4: exendin-4, IL-1β: interleukin-1β, IL-6: interleukin 6, TGF-β: 
transforming growth factor-β, TNF: tumor necrosis factor, TZP: tirzepatide.
