Extended Data Fig. 10 | Administration of GLP-1RAs reduces neuro­
inflammation and enhances microglia phagocytosis in APP23/PS45 mice. 
APP23/PS45 double transgenic mice at the age of 6 weeks were treated with 
exendin-4 for 8 weeks, while age-matched control APP23/PS45 mice received 
vehicle solution. The mice were sacrificed after Morris water maze behavioral 
tests, and the brains were homogenized in lysis buffer or dissected, fixed, and 
sectioned. The levels of IL-1β (a), IL-6 (b), TNF (c) and TGF-β (d) were measured by 
performing ELISA. n = 4 independent experiments; A two-tailed student’s t-test 
was performed for statistical analysis. (e) Representative brain sections of the 
control and exendin-4 injected APP23/PS45 mice sacrificed immediately after 
behavioral analysis. Scale bar represents 100μm. The squares (dashed white 
lines) correspond to enlarged areas in each image. (f) Quantification of CD68 
expressions in APP23/PS45 mouse brains, the number represents mean ± s.e.m., 
n = 30 mice total, A two-tailed student’s t-test was performed for statistical 
analysis. All the results are expressed as mean ± s.e.m. EX-4: exendin-4, IL-1β: 
interleukin-1β, IL-6: interleukin 6, TGF-β: transforming growth factor-β,  
TNF: tumor necrosis factor.
